{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"65c8cd19-6002-4f50-a438-9381a676ee5e","content":"You're on MSTest 3.8.2 which supports **constructor injection** for `TestContext`. Here's the recommended pattern:\n\n```csharp\n[TestClass]\npublic class MyTests : IAsyncInitialization, IAsyncCleanup\n{\n    private readonly TestContext _testContext;\n    private HttpClient _client;\n\n    // Synchronous init via constructor — TestContext is injected automatically\n    public MyTests(TestContext testContext)\n    {\n        _testContext = testContext;\n    }\n\n    // Async init — runs after constructor, before each test\n    public async Task InitializeAsync()\n    {\n        _client = new HttpClient();\n        await _client.GetAsync(\"https://example.com/health\");\n    }\n\n    // Async cleanup — runs after each test\n    public async Task CleanupAsync()\n    {\n        _client?.Dispose();\n        await Task.CompletedTask;\n    }\n\n    [TestMethod]\n    public void TestSomething()\n    {\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_testContext);\n        Assert.IsNotNull(_client);\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- **Constructor injection**: MSTest 3.x injects `TestContext` automatically — no `[TestInitialize]` or property setter needed.\n- **`IAsyncInitialization`**: Implement for async per-test setup (replaces `[TestInitialize] async Task`).\n- **`IAsyncCleanup`**: Implement for async per-test teardown.\n- You can still use `[ClassInitialize]` / `[ClassCleanup]` for one-time static setup if needed.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9f94a560-07a7-45e5-b52c-2ffffca34e27","outputTokens":393,"requestId":"800F:28893:16DBF79:183D65E:6A046100"},"id":"b602c58b-b9e4-4d93-ab8a-1117d2ef12c2","timestamp":"2026-05-13T11:31:21.427Z","parentId":"05496018-ad15-4710-b08c-a55ef1d68876"}
